rComments: I took this class in 2009. It wasn't that bad... boring busy work. Evaluation was based on participation in a mandatory grammar tutorial, 500-word response essays, and a longer final essay. The format has since changed. No knowledge of history necessary - just had to know how to write. I had a good TA and ended up with an 88. Class average was C-.

When I took his class I found it really boring. The only reason I did well is because I am good at history. But lectures were boring and if 270 people were registered in the class only 50-100 students would come. TA's were online. They would grade our papers and give us feedbacks. Writing is workshop useless and boring.

Overall he's just ok. The course is based completely off of online readings and you hand in weekly assignments online. Lectures are boring - goes around in circles and discusses the same/similar things every lecture. Bizarre accent but understandable. 300 people were in the class but only 50-100 came to lectures.Dont go - its practically all online

he was a nice prof..and cool looking too; lols he actually can pull the bald look off really well *thumbsup. well over all teh course is mostly discussion; so seriouly dun have to go. Digresses alot! entire class is discussion. Tut are useful though, to learn how to write better. Readings meh, not the best, but dun have to pay so good. and NO EXAM!

One of my fav, profs ever. Extremely learned and so captivating,although he tends to ramble sometimes. Follow instructions and take notes. It's easy not to want to but it will def. help on the weekly assignments and final essay. Do the readings and he enjoys participation. Warning- it is writing intensive and comes with a stupid grammar workshop!

no textbook, and weekly online assignments that can be pretty confusing. if you don't do them on time your screwed and its really easy not to want to do them. lectures were useless all he did was ramble about Armania which had nothin to do with the course. If its ur first class of the day stay home and sleep there rather than the hall.

I found professor Bonakdarian's lectures to be really interesting. Although His101 required a lot more writing than I had anticipated, I think it was worth it because the assignments taught me how to analytically think and write. It is an intensive course but I learned a lot from this class.
would LOVE to take more classes with him. He's absolutely amazing :) !!!
